@startuml USER_JOURNEY
title 
Human Operator Journey (What to do & when)
Simplified Agile Workflow
end title

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #333333
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #C8E6C9
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #FFCDD2
skinparam ActivityDiamondBorderColor #333333
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFF3CD
skinparam NoteBorderColor #333333

legend right
  **ACTOR COLOR KEY:**
  |<back:#C8E6C9>    </back>| **HUMAN** (Actions the operator physically types)
  |<back:#E8F5E9>    </back>| **Human-Dependent Domain**
  |<back:#FFE082>    </back>| <<GATE>> **Manual Checkpoint** (Mandatory Review)
  |<back:#FFCDD2>    </back>| **Logic Decision / Branch**
  | **<color:#2e7d32>/workflow</color>** | **Human-Triggered Command**
  | **<color:#c62828>/workflow</color>** | **Agent-Triggered Command** (or Sandbox)
endlegend

start

:Write one-line Vision script
----
**Context:** The foundational constraint layer. This single line dictates 
Scope Boundaries. Anything falling outside this Vision during P5-P7 
development loops will be forcefully rejected by the Agent.
**File:** `product/PRD.md` 
**Action:** Open the file natively inside your IDE. Navigate to the top mapping 
block titled `# Vision`. Delete any placeholder text and type a single, highly 
explicit sentence describing the core functionality of the MVP application you 
intend to build. Do not write extensive UI layout preferences here; constrain 
the instruction purely to the macro backend application logic.;
note right
    **Architecture Constraint Rule:** 
    An ambiguous or multi-paragraph Vision script will cascade 
    into endless system execution loop drift natively in Phase B. 
    The narrower the baseline parameter constraint, the faster 
    and significantly stabler the MVP deploy time will be.
end note

:Execute **<color:#2e7d32>/seed</color>** to validate workspace
----
**Context:** Environment verification checkpoint. Guarantees the CI simulator 
(`make check`) and physical repo hierarchy match the expected baseline state 
before any code generation protocols can fire.
**File:** `IDE Chat Console`
**Action:** Open your primary IDE chat console. Type exactly `/seed` and hit enter 
to fire the initialization webhook. The Agent will immediately spin up and run 
a validation sequence spanning your `pyproject.toml`, `Makefile`, and the `process/` 
directory tree. Wait approximately 10 seconds for the Agent to respond confirming 
all parameters pass the G0 verification gate before proceeding.;
note left
    **Agent Autonomy Subroutine:**
    While you wait, the Agent natively initializes 
    the core operational state trackers (`PROGRESS.md` 
    & `/archives`), establishing the literal `G0` Verification 
    mathematical baseline the app acts upon.
end note

partition "Phase A (P0-P4): Planning & Governance" #E8F5E9 {
    :Execute **<color:#2e7d32>/plan</color>**
    ----
    **Context:** Absorbs your Vision limits into strict verifiable logic. Generates 
    the fundamental Architecture rules (`ARCH.md`) that strictly govern what 
    dependencies and logic structures the Agent is allowed to code.
    **File:** `IDE Chat Console`
    **Action:** Return to the IDE chat console and execute the `/plan` command. 
    The Agent will cross-referencing your `# Vision` against its internal constraints, 
    halting roughly 30 seconds later to output a massive proposed mapping. Specifically 
    look for it to generate the `S-V###` master Story backlog alongside the initial 
    foundational architecture drafts. Do not execute any further commands until it 
    explicitly requests your visual review.;
    
    note right
        **Agent Autonomy Subroutine:**
        The Process Steward autonomously absorbs 
        your vision. It begins dynamically updating files:
         - Converts vision into a Story Backlog `S-V###`
         - Maps required API structures in `contracts/`
         - Drafts global limits inside `ARCH.md`
    end note
    
    if (Is the Agent unsure about a design logic choice?) then (yes)
      :Execute **<color:#2e7d32>/advise</color>** or **<color:#c62828>/explore</color>**
      ----
      **Context:** Prevents hallucination. When encountering major unknowns, 
      this sandbox forces the Agent to parse filesystems and read dependencies 
      *without* unpredictably altering source code.
      **File:** `IDE Chat Console`
      **Action:** If the Agent's generated Plan contains hallucinatory drift or you wish 
      to override a design choice (e.g. using a different database ORM), explicitly type 
      your concerns into chat. You can use `/advise` to ask for structured rules logic, 
      or `/explore` to force the Agent to dive into the codebase safely. Ensure the Agent 
      formally logs a `D-###` architectural Decision ratifying your choice before moving on.;
      note left
          **Sandbox Engine:**
          Typing `/explore` physically detaches the execution 
          head from the `P0-P7` framework phase sequence, 
          letting the system generate "throwaway" test scripts 
          in `/tmp` safely with zero database risk.
      end note
    else (no)
    endif
    
    :**Review & Approve** the Plan <<GATE>>
    ----
    **Context:** The Point-Of-No-Return for architecture. Once approved, `ARCH.md` 
    becomes officially `Read-Only` during active development, locking out rewrites.
    **Files:** `product/PRD.md` & `product/ARCH.md`
    **Action:** You must physically open both `product/PRD.md` and `product/ARCH.md` 
    inside your editor. Read through the generated Story sequences and the explicit rules 
    constraints. If they perfectly align with your target MVP scope, return to the chat 
    console and explicitly type "Approved". This formal handshake permanently locks the primary 
    architecture files into Read-Only mode for the remainder of the active development pipeline.
    **Governance:** If you manually overwrite any boundaries inside `ARCH.md` during 
    this physical review, you MUST manually append a trace log [UTC | Actor | Change] 
    to the bottom of the document before proceeding.;
    note right
        **Governance Lockdown:**
        Once `ARCH.md` receives human approval loop clearance, 
        the repository assumes strict execution mode. Any 
        subsequent unapproved Human manipulations directly altering 
        the baseline logic will crash the Agent execution engine.
    end note
    note left #FFCDD2
        **ANTI-PATTERN: Scope Creep**
        Never physically approve a massive S-### Story that 
        would take a human longer than 1 day to build natively. 
        If proposed scope is massive, immediately REJECT the 
        plan and command the Agent to slice the feature tighter.
    end note
}

partition "Phase B (P5-P7): Heavy Execution Loop" #E8F5E9 {
    repeat
        :Execute **<color:#2e7d32>/next</color>**
        ----
        **Context:** The highly-constrained Just-In-Time (JIT) execution trigger. 
        Safely constricts the Agent's autonomy window to exactly one single Task 
        checklist (`T-###`) from the tracker to prevent rogue code sprawl.
        **File:** `IDE Chat Console`
        **Action:** Open the IDE chat console and physically type the `/next` macro command. 
        This acts as the master execution trigger. The Agent will immediately parse the 
        `PROGRESS.md` logic array, locate the next unresolved `T-###` atomic task, and 
        autonomously execute against it. You do not need to provide any further context 
        snippets or file paths; the Agent natively tracks the exact file requirements 
        completely autonomously based on its JIT loop array.;
        
        note left
            **Agent Autonomy Subroutine:**
            Behind the scenes, the Process Steward is natively:
            1. Slicing S-V### Stories into atomic Tasks
            2. Writing physical Python implementations
            3. Running test verifications via `make check`
            4. Updating evidence trace logs in `PROGRESS.md`
        end note
        
        if (Did the Agent classify the active Task as HIGH-RISK?) then (yes)
            :Explicit Human Risk Override <<GATE>>
            ----
            **Context:** The JIT Engine drafted a task that alters destructive logic 
            boundaries (e.g. dropping database columns, rewriting deployment scripts). 
            Execution is permanently paralyzed until granted permission.
            **File:** `process/PROGRESS.md`
            **Action:** Read the task payload in the tracker. You must literally type 
            "Approve" in the IDE chat to release the Agent to execute the dangerous code.;
        else (no)
        endif

        if (Does the Agent detect Contract Drift during dev?) then (Yes (System Paralyzed))
            :Execute **<color:#c62828>/ccr</color>** workflow <<GATE>>
            ----
            **Context:** The master safeguard against "Silent Drift". If reality 
            deviates from `ARCH.md` laws, the Agent immediately halts logic execution 
            until a human expressly rewrites the hard specs.
            **File:** `process/PROGRESS.md`
            **Action:** If execution halts on a CCR Block, immediately open `process/PROGRESS.md` 
            and read the exact `CCR-###` entry the Agent raised detailing the contract mismatch. 
            You hold sovereign override authority. In the IDE chat, you must explicitly state how 
            to proceed. Typing "APPROVE CCR" permanently overrides the API layout in the `ARCH` 
            contracts. Typing "REJECT CCR" forces the Agent to discard its logic branch and 
            rewrite the code to honor the original baseline structure.;
            
            note right
                **Contract Defense Logic:**
                If a 3rd party API updates or logic fails entirely, the 
                Agent cannot 'hack' a workaround without Human consent.
                 1. **Approve:** Rewrites the ARCH contracts to match.
                 2. **Reject:** Forces Agent to find a different path.
                 3. **Defer:** Abandons the active task loop sequence.
                --
                **Traceability Governance:** If you APPROVE a change 
                to the Contract baseline, you are strictly required 
                to append exactly one new tracking matrix row to the 
                `CONTRACTS.md` Traceability log explicitly defining why.
            end note
            note left #FFCDD2
                **ANTI-PATTERN: Blind Approval**
                Never blindly type "APPROVE" to bypass a system blocker. 
                If the Agent deletes a required field struct merely 
                to bypass a failing QA test, your downstream logic 
                will permanently collapse. Read the physical proposal.
            end note
        else (No (Smooth Execution))
            :Wait for Agent to finish execution loop
            ----
            **Context:** JIT processing in flight. The Steward sequentially writes 
            logic, writes identical tests, and hammers the local `make check` suite 
            hundreds of times until code behaves 100% deterministically.
            **File:** `Terminal logs`
            **Action:** Physically remove your hands from the keyboard. The Process 
            Steward is currently writing raw logic, drafting parallel unit tests, and 
            repeatedly hammering the local validations. You will see terminal windows 
            flashing rapidly as the automated QA verification engine repeatedly passes 
            or fails. Absolutely do not interrupt the Agent mid-flight, nor type code into 
            the IDE, until it explicitly issues a "Task Completed" response natively in chat.;
        endif

        if (Is the Agent hallucinating / ignoring architecture frameworks?) then (yes)
            :Agent Hard Reset Override
            ----
            **Context:** LLMs inevitably drift. If the Agent repeatedly violates 
            Read-Only boundaries or ignores the PRD limits entirely, it has lost focus.
            **File:** `IDE Chat Console`
            **Action:** Interrupt the Agent. Paste the exact "Hard Reset Sequence" prompt: 
            "Stop. Re-read process/PROCESS_REFERENCE.md and process/PROGRESS.md. Resume 
            in Process Steward mode. Do not modify approval files without explicit approval.";
            note left #FFCDD2
                **ANTI-PATTERN: The Runaway AI**
                Never let an Agent argue with the framework rules. 
                If it attempts to bypass `ARCH.md` without CCR, or 
                forgets its identity as the Process Steward, fire 
                the Hard Reset script to reboot the workflow state.
            end note
        else (no)
        endif

        if (Is the LLM context window dragging or bloated?) then (yes)
            :Execute **<color:#c62828>/archive</color>**
            ----
            **Context:** Mitigates severe LLM context degradation. Once the live memory 
            buffer exceeds limits, trimming log history restores baseline inference speeds.
            **File:** `IDE Chat Console`
            **Action:** If you notice the Agent's response times degrading significantly or 
            it begins routinely forgetting specific constraints, the live memory block is 
            bloated. Open the chat console and type the `/archive` macro. The system will 
            aggressively sweep all successfully completed `[x]` legacy tasks out of `PROGRESS.md` 
            and shift them permanently into the `archive/` data structure, instantly 
            restoring lightning-fast inference performance.;
            note right
                **Mathematical Governor:**
                The `/archive` system absolutely never touches or deletes 
                functional Source Code. It strictly flushes dead operational 
                metadata tracking strings from the root `PROGRESS.md` array.
            end note
        else (no)
        endif

    repeat while (Is the active Story completely executed?) is (No)
    
    :**Review** Story Acceptance Criteria <<GATE>>
    ----
    **Context:** Deep Validation Check. Ensures the automated mathematical tests 
    the Agent passed actually structurally translate to a functionally usable 
    Human interface as mapped out by the baseline scope limits.
    **File:** Local `app` Execution binary (or UI)
    **Action:** The Agent has formally requested a Story boundary check. You must 
    boot up the native application environment locally (via `npm run dev` or the 
    Python binary equivalent). Open your browser or target interface and physically 
    stress-test the raw logic the Agent just built. Cross-reference your results 
    exactly against the explicit Acceptance Criteria mapped in the `PRD.md` file 
    to determine if the logic passes standard QA metrics.;
    note right #FFCDD2
        **ANTI-PATTERN: Fake QA**
        An automated "Green Build" passing `make check` 
        tests natively does NOT mean the feature actually 
        works for humans! You MUST physically interact with 
        the Interface or Outputs before typing "Passed".
    end note
    
    if (Does physical execution match the PRD boundaries?) then (Fail (Bug Found))
        :Report regression
        ----
        **Context:** This feeds physical reality back into the Agent's isolated JIT 
        engine, immediately forcing a logic rewrite or architectural bridge patch.
        **File:** `IDE Chat Console`
        **Action:** If your physical validation discovers a broken UI hook, a failed 
        backend call, or a behavioral element that does not match the strict PRD logic, 
        do not fix it yourself. Copy the raw error trace, or explicitly describe what 
        is functioning incorrectly. Paste this feedback directly into the IDE chat. This 
        immediately boots the Agent out of the review phase and throws it back into 
        a `P6: Task Iteration` patch loop.;
        note left
            **Boundary Validation Loop:**
            The Agent physically restarts the atomic 
            iteration loop, rewriting isolated application code 
            until it resolves the failing physical boundary.
        end note
    else (Pass (Valid))
        :Story Officially Passed
        ----
        **Context:** Feature officially locked. Future edits to this code block 
        will require opening a new issue block. System snaps to next Story.
        **File:** `IDE Chat Console`
        **Action:** If the physical application sequence tests out perfectly and fully 
        honors the Acceptance Criteria, formalize the conclusion. In the IDE Chat console, 
        simply state: "Passed, you may close out the active story." The Agent will 
        permanently log `S-###` as Done in the master tracker, securely save the final 
        evidence artifacts, and prime the architecture to attack the next Story block.;
    endif
}

partition "Phase C (P8-P12): Release & Deploy" #E8F5E9 {
    :Execute **<color:#2e7d32>/release</color>** <<GATE>>
    ----
    **Context:** Bridges local MVP development loops with Live environments. 
    Executes a comprehensive, unified E2E regression check across all components.
    **File:** `IDE Chat Console`
    **Action:** Once the entire Backlog array is categorically empty, open the Chat 
    console and trigger the `/release` command. This forces the Agent to break out 
    of single-feature iteration loops and run a massive End-to-End global system 
    verification patch. Wait while it executes full repository test suites. Once it 
    finishes, it will generate the formal Release Notes and stage the code branch 
    for Production mapping.;
    note right
        **Global QA Sweep Engine:**
        Inside Phase C, the system abandons atomic 
        Task-Feature level `make check` gating and runs 
        the definitive suite validations against the entire 
        unified codebase architecture simultaneously.
    end note
    
    :Deploy & Evaluate
    ----
    **Context:** Live code delivery sequence. This pushes your locked codebase 
    outward, generating real-world metrics required to seed Version 2.0.
    **File:** Your personal Cloud deployment mechanism.
    **Action:** Navigate out of the IDE and move to your preferred Production 
    deployment orchestration interface (e.g. Vercel, Fly.io, or your AWS console). 
    Connect the V-Tagged code branch to your deployment logic and physically launch 
    the live version.;
    
    if (Did the Production Server build successfully?) then (Fail (Crash))
        :Deployment Rollback Trigger
        ----
        **Context:** Escaping out of Release phase sequence. The system must 
        abandon the V### tag and draft a P0-Severity regression bug natively.
        **File:** `IDE Chat Console`
        **Action:** Tell the Agent: "Deployment failed due to [X]. Return to 
        Phase A and execute `/plan` to draft a P0 resolution Story.";
        note left
            **Backward Escape Routing:**
            A live failure explicitly kicks the 
            SDLC loop backward out of Phase C 
            forcing a brand new PRD iteration.
        end note
    else (Pass (Stable Deploy))
        :Version V### Officially Live
        ----
        **Context:** End of Version Lifecycle.
        **Action:** Evaluate telemetry and system constraints. To initiate 
        the next major product loop, you must clean `PROGRESS.md` tags, draft 
        brand new Stories into `product/PRD.md`, and physically cycle 
        all the way back up to **Phase A** to trigger `/plan` anew.;
    endif
}

stop
@enduml
